Photo, Necessity Has Nothing to Do With It -- A sampling of the more than 400 
inventions that will be on display Sept. 1-4 at the Pasadena Convention Center 
were shown this week in a preview. Above, a pair of "Exerlopers," low-stress 
running shoes mounted on two curved pieces of plastic so that the athlete's 
feet never touch the ground. For those chilly nights when Fluffy's bath time 
comes around, another inventor offers a pet dryer that uses air and not high 
temperatures to do the job. And at right, Michael Rodarte, a firefighter from 
