<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPORTS ET CETERA: SEEDED PLAYERS KNOCKED OUT OF BOYS' 12S 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two seeded players were eliminated and another defaulted in the fourth round of 
the USTA Boys' 12s national tennis tournament at Morley Field Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Trip Phillips of Midlothian, Tenn., upset Corey Guy of Portola Valley, seeded 
sixth, 6-1, 6-7, 6-4, and Raphael Jordan of Puerto Rico defeated Marc 
Urbainczyk of Lake Mary, Fla., the seeded eighth, 6-1, 7-5 to advance to 
today's quarterfinals. 
</P>
<P>
Ramin Pejan of West Vancouver, B.C., seeded seventh, defaulted because of 
illness. 
</P>
<P>
TRACK AND FIELD 
</P>
<P>
The deadline to raise $150,000 to save the San Diego State track and field 
program for this upcoming season has been extended to Aug. 22 by Athletic 
Director Fred Miller. 
</P>
<P>
Track and field was cut June 20 by Miller to save the athletic department 
$225,000. 
</P>
<P>
Walter Turner, who is heading an effort to raise the necessary funds, said that 
the group needs another $20,000 before private parties will underwrite the 
balance needed to reach $150,000. Approximately $115,000 has been raised. 
</P>
<P>
JUNIOR OLYMPICS 
</P>
<P>
Kristen Walls of San Diego finished fifth in the girls' 16-18 three-meter 
diving at the Junior Olympics in Houston, Tex. 
</P>
<P>
Walls, who graduated from Monte Vista, will compete at UCLA next season. She 
will compete in her specialty, the one-meter event, today. 
</P>
<P>
In synchronized swimming, Laurie McClelland of Spring Valley was second in the 
girls' 13-14 solo, and Emily Marsh and Julie Taylor of Spring Valley were 
fourth in the 13-14 duet. 
</P>
<P>
GOLF 
</P>
<P>
Liz Bowman of Bonita is tied for eighth after the second round of the Betsy 
Rawls Girls Junior Championships at the Hercules Country Club in Wilmington, 
Del. Bowman shot an eight-over par 80 and is nine shots behind leader Tonya 
Blosser of Athens, Ohio. 
</P>
