<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRST IMPRESSIONS: JOACHIM SPLICHAL BRINGS HIS SPECIAL TOUCH TO PATINA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RUTH REICHL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One of the most eagerly awaited restaurants of the year has finally opened. 
Joachim Splichal, who made Beverly Hills' Max au Triangle famous, has taken 
over the former Le St. Germain and turned it into Patina. The address is 5955 
Melrose Ave., Los Angeles. The number: (213) 467-1108. 
</P>
<P>
This was worth waiting for. The restaurant's barely been open a week, but it is 
already clear that Splichal's food is as exciting as it ever was, that the 
small restaurant manages to be both modern and intimate and that the prices are 
fair (entrees hover around the $20 mark). 
</P>
<P>
After one visit I can recommend the appetizer of Santa Barbara shrimp with 
mashed potatoes and truffle chips, the very peppered tuna with Asian accents 
that is served atop a tangle of vegetables, and the spectacular peach galette 
for dessert. And I can tell you that I am really looking forward to eating my 
way through the rest of the menu. RUTH REICHL 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Newly opened Patina on Melrose Avenue combines modern flair with 
intimate surroundings. ELLEN JASKOL / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
<TYPE>
<P>
