<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MEDICAL BUILDING HIT BY BOMB BLAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A medical building housing the office of a white supremacist organization in 
Glendale was hit early Thursday by a bomb explosion that shattered windows and 
caused about $5,000 damage, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
There were no reported injuries. 
</P>
<P>
The two-story structure in the 1200 block of South Glendale Avenue was shaken 
by the blast of a medium-strength bomb at 3:30 a.m., according to Capt. John 
Orr of the Glendale Fire Department's arson-explosive unit. 
</P>
<P>
Orr said that George King, a member of the League of Pace Amendment Advocates, 
favoring deportation of all people who are not white Christians, told 
authorities that he believes the bomb was directed at his organization. 
</P>
<P>
The case has been turned over to the FBI because it may have been politically 
motivated, Orr said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
