<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: BRADLEY PICKS COMRIE FOR METRO RAIL PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Mayor Tom Bradley on Thursday appointed City Administrative Officer 
Keith Comrie to represent the city on a three-member cost-cutting panel to 
oversee the beleagured Metro Rail project. 
</P>
<P>
The board will monitor construction on the first 4 miles of the subway, which a 
Los Angeles County Transportation Commission audit found to be $135 million, or 
10%, over budget. The overrun triggered a clause in the funding contract 
between the transportation commission, the Southern California Rapid Transit 
District and the city that establishes a committee with authority to direct 
economy measures on the project, which is two years behind. 
</P>
<P>
Supervisor Pete Schabarum or his alternate, political consultant Mike Lewis, 
represents the LACTC. The SCRTD has not yet appointed its representative. The 
board's first meeting is scheduled for Aug. 17. 
</P>
</TEXT>
