<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 43-year-old San Diego man died Wednesday night when he was struck by a car in 
Rancho Penasquitos. 
</P>
<P>
Charles Francis Goeb was at Stoney Creek Road when he attempted to cross Carmel 
Mountain Road. He was struck by a northbound car in the 10300 block of Carmel 
Mountain Road. The car was driven by Patrick J. Moore, 24, of Rancho 
Penasquitos, said San Diego police spokesman Bill Robinson. 
</P>
<P>
Moore was arrested on suspicion of vehicular manslaughter and driving under the 
influence, Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
Moore is being held in County Jail in lieu of $10,000 bail. He is scheduled to 
be arraigned today. 
</P>
<P>
Goeb, who died at the scene, is the 24th pedestrian to be killed on San Diego 
streets this year, Robinson said. 
</P>
