<HEADLINE>
<P>
LA HABRA'S MAY TRAILS BY 3 IN STATE OPEN GOLF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob May of La Habra shot a 72 to slip into third-place tie Thursday after three 
rounds of the California State Open in Rancho Mirage. 
</P>
<P>
May, who had rounds of 65 and 69, is tied with Ted Lehmann of Thousand Oaks. 
Both are three strokes back at 205. 
</P>
<P>
Brad Bell of Sacramento had an eagle-3 to shoot six-under 66 to take the lead. 
</P>
</TEXT>
