<HEADLINE>
<P>
FULLERTON'S VAN DORTRECHT PERFECT IN SOFTBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ann Van Dortrecht pitched a perfect game, striking out all 21 batters, as the 
Southern California Ballhogs defeated the Tucson Angels, 2-0, Thursday in the 
first round of the 19-and-under national softball tournament in Sioux Falls, 
S.D. 
</P>
<P>
Van Dortrecht, who plays for Cal State Fullerton, didn't come close to walking 
a batter. 
</P>
<P>
The Ballhogs broke a scoreless tie in the top of the seventh. Lisa Sciarrino of 
Western High School and Pam Barr of Diamond Bar singled and both later scored 
on an error. 
</P>
<P>
In other first-round game: 
</P>
<P>
Gordon's Panthers of Cypress defeated Ripco Sonics of Illinois, 13-4. Missy 
Gyde of Kennedy High School had two hits and two runs batted in. 
</P>
</TEXT>
