<P>
Newspaper Chain to Go Public: Central Newspapers Inc., the Indianapolis-based 
newspaper chain that controls the Arizona Republic and Phoenix Gazette, is 
going public. Under the plan, about 200,000 shares of Central Newspapers' Class 
A stock will be available for sale. Currently, those shares have no voting 
rights. But under changes approved by shareholders last month, those shares 
will have one-tenth the voting rights of Class B shares. The Class B stock will 
not be available for public sale. 
