<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: REAL ESTATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Michael Flagg, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Burke Commercial Real Estate, Orange, reported revenue of $350 million for its 
1989 fiscal year. The real estate brokerage increased its number of 
transactions by 20% this year, the company said. 
</P>
<P>
Burke operates in Orange and Riverside counties. The firm handled the 
second-largest transaction in its 20-year history this year, the $19.7-million 
sale of State College Park business center in Anaheim. The property was bought 
by Burke clients Hutton Development Co. and Japanese investor Tobishima Co. 
</P>
</TEXT>
