<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
U.S. FIRM GIVEN CHINA CONCESSIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BEIJING 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China granted a series of concessions to the first U.S. company to agree to 
invest in the country since Beijing's military crackdown in early June, the 
president of the company said today. 
</P>
<P>
Mohammad Malekpour, president of privately owned, U.S.-based MGM Development 
Co., said in an interview that he won several "advantages" for a contract he 
signed Tuesday to develop an industrial park. 
</P>
<P>
"China wants this project to be an example that it has not changed its 
open-door policy," Malekpour said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
