<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
TALLEY TO SIGN BUFFALO CONTRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
FREDONIA, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Buffalo Bills reached a tentative contract agreement with linebacker Darryl 
Talley, the last of five starters from the 1988 season who were holdouts this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
Talley was expected to report to camp either today or Saturday and sign a 
three-year deal that will increase his base salary from $315,000 to $500,000. 
</P>
<P>
Another veteran expected to report today was cornerback Derrick Burroughs, who 
agreed to a three-year deal worth an average of $400,000 per season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
